How to Setup Virtual Environment in Ubuntu  Machine

# Make sure Python is installed on your machine 
python3 --version

sudo at pinstall python3-pip -y

# Install python3 Virtual Environment
sudo apt install python3-venv -y or pip3 install virtualenv

# Install Venv Dependencies
pip install psutils

sudo apt update

# Create Virtual Environment
python3 -m venv myenv

# Activate Python Virtual Environment
source myenv/bin/activate

# Venv De-Activation
Deactivate
